body:
Passes that run after `ExportVerilog` can query incorrect names from the IR because names in the IR may not be updated.  We should be making sure that the IR after `ExportVerilog` matches whatever we emit or we need to add `verilogName` attributes to anything which is renamed.

### Example Problem with `HWExportModuleHierarchy`

Consider the following example for the `HWExportModuleHierarchy` pass (which runs after `ExportVerilog`).  This has two Verilog keyword collisions.  The innermost module is called "module" and the instance name of that module is also called "module":

```mlir
hw.module @module(%in: i1) -> (out: i1) {
  hw.output %in : i1
}

hw.module @MainDesign(%in: i1) -> (out: i1) {
  %0 = hw.instance "module" @module(in: %in: i1) -> (out: i1)
  hw.output %0 : i1
}

hw.module @TestHarness() attributes {firrtl.moduleHierarchyFile = #hw.output_file<"testharness_hier.json", excludeFromFileList>} {
  %0 = hw.constant 1 : i1
  hw.instance "main_design" @MainDesign(in: %0: i1) -> (out: i1)
}
```

This produces the following Verilog with properly mangled names:

```verilog
module module_0(	// Foo.mlir:1:1
  input  in,
  output out);

  assign out = in;	// Foo.mlir:2:3
endmodule

module MainDesign(	// Foo.mlir:5:1
  input  in,
  output out);

  module_0 module_0 (	// Foo.mlir:6:8
    .in  (in),
    .out (out)
  );
endmodule

module TestHarness();	// Foo.mlir:10:1
  wire main_design_out;	// Foo.mlir:12:3

  MainDesign main_design (	// Foo.mlir:12:3
    .in  (1'h1),	// Foo.mlir:11:8
    .out (main_design_out)
  );
endmodule
```

The IR after `ExportVerilog` includes an updated name for the module, but not the instance:

```mlir
  hw.module @module(%in: i1) -> (out: i1) attributes {verilogName = "module_0"} {
    hw.output %in : i1
  }
  hw.module @MainDesign(%in: i1) -> (out: i1) {
    %module.out = hw.instance "module" @module(in: %in: i1) -> (out: i1)
    hw.output %module.out : i1
  }
```

This then results in `HWExportModuleHierarchy` producing JSON which is not correct with respect to the emitted Verilog (the innermost "instance_name" should be "module_0":

```json
{
  "instance_name": "TestHarness",
  "module_name": "TestHarness",
  "instances": [
    {
      "instance_name": "main_design",
      "module_name": "MainDesign",
      "instances": [
        {
          "instance_name": "module",
          "module_name": "module_0",
          "instances": []
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
```
